Uninstall Anaconda
https://unixcop.com/how-to-uninstall-anaconda-on-ubuntu/
First of all, you have to install the package anaconda-clean by running the following command:
conda install anaconda-clean
Next step is to clean all anaconda related files and directories with the tool we just installed (anaconda-clean):
anaconda-clean --yes
Also removes the entire anaconda directory as shown below:
rm -rf ~/anaconda3
NOTE: anaconda-clean tool creates a backup of files/dirs after removing the anaconda files, so remove it with the following command:
rm -rf ~/.anaconda_backup

Download and install Anaconda
bash Anaconda3-2022.10-Linux-x86_64.sh

update conda enviroment
conda update -n base -c defaults conda

create conda environment
conda create --name textoir_env

activate environment
conda activate textoir_env

if pip not installed, the install it using:
sudo apt install python3-pip

goto /mywork/dev/nlp/lm/textior/TEXTOIR/open_intent_detection and install requirements
pip install -r requirements.txt


if conflict with mkl_fft try:
https://pypi.org/project/mkl-fft/
conda install -c intel mkl_fft
or
pip install mkl_fft dpcpp_cpp_rt==2021.2 



